Package: tulaverse
Type: Package
Title: Stata-Inspired Console Output and Visualization for R
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Jeremy", "Freese", email = "jfreese@stanford.edu",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides Stata-inspired console output for regression models,
    descriptive statistics, and frequency tables. The tula() function produces
    formatted regression output — including a model fit header and coefficient
    table with factor variable grouping — for a wide range of model types
    (lm, glm, negative binomial, ordered regression, multinomial logit, Cox
    proportional hazards, conditional logistic regression, quantile
    regression, fixed effects models, tobit and survival regression,
    survey-weighted GLMs, and constrained estimation). The tulatab() function produces one-way frequency tables
    and two-way crosstabulations with optional means and other summary
    statistics. Plotting functions (tulaplot(), theme_tula()) provide
    ggplot2 integration with defaults closer to those used by Stata.
